End of Evangelion is literally just two more hours baked from the same dough-like substance as the final 10 episodes of the show, like one of those "schizo memes" made by 16 year olds who pretend to post on /x/. Still, pretty enjoyable, glad I watched it, just can't be mesmerized

"Undertale" the vidya does the "traditional narrative culminating into psychoanalytic deconstruction" a lot better, there is simply no need to extend it for so long, one single final episode of "here are Shinji's emotions + a collage of Biblical events" would have been sufficient

The true culmination of the series is Shinji being trapped into the sphere realizing the Evangelion is a biological entity after tasting blood, also breaking off the armor and revealing its nature. Only good part of EoE movie is Asuke ascending into pure bloodlust during battle.
I mean I can see how this is a reasonable thing to believe, but if I have to be 100% honest I think this just means getting deceived by external appearances, pls explain why you think so

Like if you watch it with an even *slightly* critical eye, you just can't get mesmerized by it, it's very stimulating, but it's like Rozanov said about Tolstoy trying to "fascinate" his reader and impress him, it's just external appearances with basic psychoanalysis as substance
